task.summary: Default task
Small improvements for CIL-771
5.2.5 final checkin. Updated online help. Found an edge case where formatting a string lost a few linefeeds.
Creating 5.2.5
Bad version number in QDL pom.xml.
Merge from 5.2.5 branch. CIL-1225
CIL-1174. Use default Java trust manager as the default.
Support for SciAuth
Changed how debugging works so it is more modular.
Added module to QDL for basic set operations. Found tiny issue with test not running in certain cases.
Made sets support in QDL official with tests and documentation.
Needed to update size function for sets.
More set support tests. Found lots of cruft in the documents. re-ran the parser build.
Found and solved an edge case with lexical tokens in the parser.

Updated unit tests, added locking to cleanup threads. Rough count of QDL unit tests puts it at about 1875, in addition to many many for OA4MP. Lots of documentation upgrades/revisions. Parser regenerated.
Cleanup can now be disabled. Found and fixed another issue with the parser -- with regression tests.

Wide-ranging house cleaning. Most all of this boils down to rectifying insufficient error messages in cases that a wrong argument, wrong number of arguments etc. were used. Now it gives much much better feedback on the type of error. Re-ran the parsers to make sure everything was rebuilt with the latest version of ANTLR, since that has a few bug fixes that possibly (though very unlikely) could affect us.
Mostly getting ducks in a row before 5.2.6.
Some more cleanup. Haad to reorder execution of a few methods.
Removed some very dead code. Tweaked listing.
Finally reproduced really annoying terminal bug and fixed it. Also found one edge case for null arguments that was not handled.
More pruning. Twiddled exceptions to give better messages
More house cleaning and pruning. Added more tests for sets and beefed up serialization test so it is not haphazard. Added a complete set of server mode regression tests.
Cut out a ton of dead code and useless comments. Found edge case in parser, so re-ran ANTLR build. test included in case of regression.
Changed order of operations, so yet another parser rebuild. Changed some formatting, tweaked a few tests. Updated manuals.
Removed extra character from parser. Changed MailUtil so it won't barf out stack traces for everything.
CIL-1268. Added tracking original state so certain errors can be backed out of generally across all components. No internal server errors, e.g., should ever invalidated tokens.

Far-reaching upgrade to error handling. Now pretty much every error in QDL can report its source code location. Waited until 5.2.6 was out the door ("just in case") since this impacts all error handling. This will make debugging scripts a lot nicer. Seems to just work. :) :)
Weirdly enjoyable day of reworking documentation and examples. Very useful,normally very dull.
removed a bunch of extra whitespace from help. Added better error messages in JWT singing utility in case the wrong keys are found (indicating usually that the wrong VO is being used by the client).
Help changes, fixed an edge case with parsing of empty statements. Added line reading for files.
Added module for databse access and revised some tests.
Renamed a couple of classes to be far more descriptive.

Rewrote list processing in QDL. This originally used TreeSet in certain places -- the slowest possible Java Collection. It became clear that those components were among actually the most frequently used in practice. TreeSet was almost compeltely replaced with ArrayList -- the fastest Java Collection. Speed increase by 25% right off the bat in unit tests from 17 seconds to 13 seconds.

Last bit of housekeeping in QDL before turning my attention fully to CIL-1081 and delegation. Wanted to add some regression tests and check a few edge cases so this can be unattended for the next bit.
New documentation did not get added to git. Adding it.
Housekeeping and performance in QDL. Changed to much faster indexing options. Renamed a class.
Minor changes (convenience method to remove boilerplate that was proliferating).
Spplit up and renamed a QDL function that was being too overloaded for its own good.
Check in before travel.
Removed redundant functions. Added a new operator for << (mostly syntactic sugar).
Changed a delimiter. Hopefully improved logging messages by making them more succinct.
Clean up. Added small tweak to a JSON utility.
Refactoring that was loooong overdue and looks far worse than it is: This simply renamed a widely used class and uses delegation now (has_a not is_a relationship) for it.
Added extraction (a utility). Test included. Cleaned up some cruft in the parser.
Added extraction operator with documentation and tests.
Updated help mostly.
More documentation updates. Improved part of QDL IDE so it makes logical sense and not just ad hoc. Fixed some formatting issues.
Managed to delete large block of help. Restoring.
